🚀 KUBERNETES SERVICES (Master this)
🔹 1. What is it?

A Service in Kubernetes provides a stable network endpoint to access a group of pods.

🔹 2. Why we use it?

Because pods are dynamic — their IPs change when they restart, so we need a stable way to access them.

🔹 3. Where it is used?
Communication between services (backend ↔ database)
Exposing applications to users
Load balancing traffic across pods
🔹 4. How it works?

Service uses labels to identify pods and forwards traffic to them, providing a stable IP and DNS name.

🎤 Interview Answer (Base)

“Kubernetes Service provides a stable way to access pods. Since pod IPs change dynamically, services use labels to route traffic and ensure consistent communication.”
